{
  "text": "The ORB technique is based on improved F AST and the Binary Robust Independent Elementary Features BRIEF feature detector techniques to extract points of interest by using a binary string [CITATION_1] . Since F AST and BRIEF process quickly, the ORB will also be fast [CITATION_2] . While the F AST technique is not sensitive to noise and is highly reliable for identifying feature points, it does not provide an orientation. However, ORB incorporates orientation into F AST with the oF AST algorithm. The BRIEF approach finds descriptors around each feature point by using a binary coding method [CITATION_3] , which is simple and requires less memory compared to SIF T and SU RF [CITATION_4] . Consider p is a smoothed image patch defined on the size of S * S (Where S contains the coordinates of pixels) round feature points and a binary random selected test defined as \u03c4 ,",
  "correct_citation": {
